page.title: 19My Typical Day.
page.content: I woke up on Sunday Morning around 8.30 am and listened to the News on the radio. I got washed and cleaned my teeth. Then I had my breakfast. Then when I had finished, I went out side then Andrew Beeton came to play . Then we went inside and went up stairs to play snooker. I won easily. I said "Do you want another game?" He said "No. Let's go in the water." So we went outside in the water. We went under the tunnel. I had found some duck eggs before so we went up to look at the eggs.The mother was still on the nest. When we had looked at the nest we went back up the tunnel and went in the house to look at the time. It was time for him to go . He went home . Then I had my dinner. By Gary Frost, Age 11.
